Well that was painless.  Turns out there are lots of #green electricty providers.  #Ecotricity is simply the most expensive.  Just switched to @bulbenergy's 100% renewable, saving ¬£300 p.a.!

Oh boy.  After years and years, finally got round to checking out @DaleVince.  Not at all liking what I‚Äôm seeing, Dale.  Very pleased to be "moving on" from #Ecotricity today.  #unethical https://t.co/Ubaidymgjp
After years of paying through the nose for #Ecotricity, I am SO much looking forward to junking them tomorrow morning.  #unethical
So much looking forward to getting rid of #unethical #Ecotricity on Tuesday morning (and paying far less, too).

And yes, I still want @DaleVince‚Äôs private cellphone number, so I can bombard you, Dale, with junk texts.  After all, I do have that right, you know.  Or maybe you didn‚Äôt ready my T&Cs?  (they're the same as #ecotricity's)

I didn‚Äôt know I was giving #Ecotricity permission to pass my private details to some anonymous third party (and who will they in turn give them to?)  But hey, somewhere in the T&Cs it probably gives them Droit du Seigneur over my firstborn.  My stupid mistake #unethical
So really, the only difference between #ecotricity and ‚Äì oh any other electricity company ‚Äì is that they charge you 40% more.  They‚Äôre certainly no more #ethical.

Hidden away in all this verbiage (you‚Äôve read every word, right?) is a catch-all clause that gives them the right to violate your privacy in any way they so choose.  So that‚Äôs OK then, #ecotricity?

Beware #Ecotricity.  Not only will they charge you a 40% premium on your electricity bills.  But they will also bombard you with junk advertising texts.  ‚ÄúYou have agreed to our terms and conditions‚Äù, they say. This is a 7000 word document!

@ecotricity Not getting a straight answer from you.  Very disillusioned with #Ecotricity.  Been paying a 40% premium to deal with you for years! Turns out you‚Äôre just as #unethical as any other multinational. :( Feel mugged.
@ecotricity The texts say they‚Äôre from #Ecotricity.  So that‚Äôs untrue, too?  #unethical

@ecotricity #ecotricity  An afterthought.  Why don‚Äôt you give me @DaleVince‚Äôs private cellphone no?  I will then send him two unwanted junk texts every day.  If #ecotricity think that's OK to do to their customers, I'm sure Dale won't mind a bit. #unethical

@ecotricity #ecotricity is allegedly an ethical company, that‚Äôs why I deal with you.  Abusing my data like this is a violation of trust.  I hope you can see that?  Or do you still maintain ‚Äúwe have the right to do that?‚Äù #unethical

@ecotricity .../... I phoned to complain #ecotricity ‚Äì this took half an hour ‚Äì and was told it wouldn‚Äôt happen again.  Another junk txt has just come in.  You‚Äôve given my personal data to a 3rd party, haven‚Äôt you?
@ecotricity You do not have - and never had had - permission to keep sending me junk texts.  You pulled me out of a meeting this am to read a junk text from #ecotricity.  .../...

@ecotricity touts itself as an ethical company. This apparently doesn‚Äôt prevent them from giving confidential customer info to 3rd parties, and sending you nuisance texts.  ‚ÄúWe have the right to do so‚Äù, they tell me.  I don't pay a premium to be treated like this.
